The paper deals with designing algorithms for the maximum matching problem, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. The paper also establishes new lower and upper bounds on the competitive ratio achievable by preemptive online algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
